# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Sample environment for a REAL eval run (tools/eval/run.py).
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in — never commit real keys.
#
# Only a live baseline/treatment run needs any of this, and a live run
# spends real API credits per call. The deterministic scorer (score.py)
# and the orchestration tests (tests/) need none of it.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# API key for whatever agent `invoke_agent_via_api` drives (Anthropic by
# default — see README.md's "Running a real eval"). Required only for a
# live run; the fake-agent tests exercised in CI never read it.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional: pin the model and a per-run cost ceiling so results are
# comparable and a runaway loop can't quietly burn credits. Consumed by
# your own invoke_agent_via_api implementation, not by run.py itself.
# AGENTHARNESS_EVAL_MODEL=
# AGENTHARNESS_EVAL_MAX_USD=
